    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I open nvim (with -u NONE), do a vsplit and move across the right buffer with j/k (or 50j / 50k), the left buffer breaks. It doesn't restore when I switch to that buffer, scroll or edit it. It sometimes restores if I close the right buffer but sometimes doesn't.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7079a8e4-67a0-437d-9bf7-6def1c3a6fb7\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim -u NONE <any 200 lines long file>\n:vsplit\nctrl-w l -- switch to the right buffer\n50j\n-- observe that the left buffer text is broken (at char 49 for me but could be at the center?)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno part of the left buffer changes when I scroll the right one\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS Tahoe 26.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew",
